President Biden spoke with German Chancellor Angela Merkel to discuss deepening relations between the United States and Germany. He emphasized his commitment to revitalizing the transatlantic alliance through NATO and the European Union, as a means to ensure collective security and promote shared democratic values. The leaders agreed to collaborate on various foreign policy issues such as Afghanistan, China, Iran, Russia, Ukraine, and the Western Balkans. They also recognized the significance of global cooperation, particularly in areas such as combatting climate change, addressing the COVID-19 pandemic, advancing health security, and promoting a sustainable global economic recovery.